{#- Trade form error fragment — banner-only. Used when form re-render is not
    applicable (HardCapException, path-aware 404 fallback, trade gone after
    form-GET). For drift-recovery cases (§5.1 cases 1, 2, 3), routes render
    the relevant form template directly with an `error_message` context var —
    the banner appears INLINE inside the form's `<td>`, so the next submit
    replaces both at once (no orphaned banner row). -#}
<tr class="trade-form-error">
  <td colspan="8">
    <div class="banner banner-degraded" role="alert">{{ error_message }}</div>
  </td>
</tr>
